<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Draft: a draft of a letter or document in the handwriting of the author ]">ADf</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Gilder Lehrman Collection, on deposit at the New-York Historical Society, New York ]">NNGL</span>: Knox Papers.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0521-0001-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0521-0001-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Knox had estimated ten days at least in his letter to GW of 5 December.</p>

</div>
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-03-02-02-pb-0565">[565]</span>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0521-0001-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0521-0001-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>20 or 21 December.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0521-0001-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0521-0001-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0521-0002" class="document">enclosure</a><span class="choice deletion" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Deleted: ' printed below' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2014-12-02]]&lt;/span&gt; ]"><img alt="deletion" src="images/deletion_mark-trans.png" style="border:none;vertical-align: text-bottom; padding-right:2px"/></span>. Knox reached Cambridge on 24 January.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0521-0001-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0521-0001-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0521-0002" class="document">enclosure</a><span class="choice deletion" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Deleted: ' printed below' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2014-12-02]]&lt;/span&gt; ]"><img alt="deletion" src="images/deletion_mark-trans.png" style="border:none;vertical-align: text-bottom; padding-right:2px"/></span> and Knox to Alexander McDougall, 17 Dec. 1775, in the Knox Papers at the Massachusetts Historical Society.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0521-0001-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0521-0001-fn-0005">5</a>
  
   <p>Lt. Col. <span class="choice correction" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Corrected from 'Allen' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2010-02-16]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">Allan</span> Maclean (17251798), a Scots Highlander who served as a British officer during the French and Indian War after being pardoned for fighting against the British at the Battle of Culloden in 1746, raised a regiment of Royal Highland Emigrants in the summer of 1775 and subsequently played a prominent role in the defense of Quebec. In May 1776 Maclean became adjutant general of the army in North America, and in June 1777 he was named military governor of Montreal with the rank of brigadier general.</p>

</div>
